Suge Knight was a dangerous man once upon a time! Karma got his ass 💯

Why would Knight have wanted to kill Eazy E? In 1991, Knight and two of his goons confronted Eazy E at Galaxy Studios at Sounds of Los Angeles Records, according to Heller’s memoir. They brought baseball bats, and they strong-armed Eazy into releasing Dr. Dre, the D.O.C. and Michel’le from Ruthless so they could sign with Knight’s Death Row label. 
In a 2003 Jimmy Kimmel appearance, Knight seemed to suggest that Eazy was murdered.

In the video above, While explaining to the host that he no longer needed to use a gun, Knight said, “See, technology is so high, right? So if you shoot somebody, you go to jail forever . . . So they got this new thing out, people sell them all the time . . . They get blood from somebody with AIDS and then they shoot you with it . . . So that’s a slow death, an Eazy-E thing, know what I mean?” Eazy-E died Mar. 26, 1995 of AIDS-related pneumonia. (Comment your thoughts below)

